  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The present study will explore a new approach to ongoing evaluation and monitoring of
      fluctuations in personality traits via commercial video games. The aim of this longitudinal
      study is to examine the influence of everyday life event on video games performance as a
      function of individual differences in gaming behavioral patterns. focusing on the ongoing
      performance vacillations of the patient on commercial video games will offer insights in to
      possibly new generation of real time assessment medium of ongoing behavior.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
